author: The Current
description:
To celebrate The Current’s 20th Anniversary, The Current’s Live Sessions Vault unlocks never-before-seen live performance videos of bands and artists who have played in our iconic studio. 

September 13 is the anniversary of the passing of Grant Hart. A Minnesota musician, Hart is best known for his time as the drummer and co-songwriter of the band Hüsker Dü, but many may not know that Hart's solo career, which began in 1988, lasted far longer than Hüsker Dü.

Watch to see the full session of Grant Hart, featuring previously unreleased footage, from when he visited The Current studio back in 2013.

Songs Performed 
00:00:00 California Zephyr
00:02:59 Awake, Arise
00:07:17 Is the Sky the Limit?

Musicians
Grant Hart — vocals, guitar
